more on the inner \ntrans=\r\nformation than mere outer change in garb...\n\nhttp://www.yogamag.net/archive=\r\ns/1992/cmay92/sssviews.shtml\n\n&quot; Sannyas is real internal transformation. It=\r\n is not mere taking geru cloth          \nfrom somebody.&#39; It is not shaving =\r\nthe head, wearing orange-coloured robes          \nand bearing a kamandalu. =\r\nThe mere taking of sannyas is no sannyas; there          \nmust be complete =\r\ntransformation of mind. &quot;\n\nIn fact, the very motto of the DLS is, &quot;Serve, L=\r\nove, Mediate, Realize&quot;, not \nrenunciate!\n\nsincerely,\nChandraprakash\n\n \n \nOn=\r\n Mon, Jun 20, 2011 at 8:32 AM, Krishnendu wrote:\n\nNamaste \n\nI have tremendo=\r\nus respect for Narasimhaji. \nStill personally I am a staunch believer in th=\r\ne sannyasa path and cannot come in \nterms to his recent arguments. \n\nAnyway=\r\n its my personal opinion. \nThought of not mentioning this on post but somet=\r\nhing was just poking me from \ninside.Maybe its my ego i dont know. \n\nI dont=\r\n want to debate just mentioned my opinion. \n\nThanks all \n\n--- In vedic-wisd=\r\nom@yahoogroups.com, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote: \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; Namaste fri=\r\nends, \n&gt; \n&gt; I wrote a critique on this sannyasa series in the past (see bel=\r\now). I \n&gt; want to make some more comments on recent posts in this series. S=\r\nome of \n&gt; the strong points made in this series have a potential to mislead=\r\n and \n&gt; instill wrong notions. \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; The argume=\r\nnts of the karma-kandins are not sound. For there cannot be \n&gt; &gt; any motive=\r\n \n&gt; &gt; or desire to act when there is the knowledge of the highest truth. He=\r\n \n&gt; &gt; does not find \n&gt; &gt; any use in the performance of karma. When one gets=\r\n a desire to know \n&gt; &gt; the atman which \n&gt; \n&gt; This notion that the paths of =\r\nkarma (action) and gyaana/jnaana \n&gt; (knowledge) oppose each other is one of=\r\n the major misconceptions of \n&gt; contemporary Vedic knowledge. I found the s=\r\name thinking at WAVES (World \n&gt; Association of Vedic Studies) conference in=\r\n Aug 2010. Some Vedic \n&gt; scholars talk about vedanta and knowledge. Some ta=\r\nlk about karma and \n&gt; actions/rituals. They think that those are two opposi=\r\nng paths. \n&gt; \n&gt; Vasishtha very clearly said at the beginning of &quot;Yoga Vaasi=\r\nshtham&quot; that \n&gt; the bird of individual self flies into the sky of undivided=\r\n and infinite \n&gt; consciousness, by flapping the two wings of karma and gyaa=\r\nna. A bird \n&gt; cannot fly with just one wing. \n&gt; \n&gt; Knowledge without action=\r\n to rid oneself of the blocking conditioning \n&gt; cannot free one. Without ac=\r\ntions, knowledge remains merely intellectual. \n&gt; Only with repeated actions=\r\n does knowledge get ingrained in one&#39;s \n&gt; consciousness so deeply that all =\r\nof one&#39;s instincts, thoughts and deeds \n&gt; are shaped by that correct knowle=\r\ndge (instead of underlying \n&gt; conditioning). Just &quot;knowing&quot; intellectually =\r\nthat a movie is not real \n&gt; and there is no need to take what happens on th=\r\ne screen seriously is not \n&gt; enough to stop you from getting startled when =\r\na really scary scene comes \n&gt; in the movie! You need to practice a lot befo=\r\nre that knowledge becomes \n&gt; natural and permanent and you stop getting sta=\r\nrtled. \n&gt; \n&gt; Similarly, actionss without knowledge are useless too. One kee=\r\nps \n&gt; performing actions forever then. One watching a movie 1000 times with=\r\nout \n&gt; the knowledge that it is unreal and should not be taken seriously wi=\r\nll \n&gt; get startled each time and enjoy the experience. \n&gt; \n&gt; In http://tiny=\r\nurl.com/homamwhydocument (from WAVES 2010 conference), I \n&gt; gave an analogy=\r\n. Suppose one needs to walk to the top of a mountain. One \n&gt; with gyaana bu=\r\nt no karma is like a person standing at the base and \n&gt; staring at the pinn=\r\nacle. He knows where to go, but he will remain at the \n&gt; base forever. One =\r\nwith karma but no gyaana is like a person going around \n&gt; the mountain fore=\r\nver. One balancing karma and gyana, i.e. engaging in \n&gt; actions cocupled wi=\r\nth the correct understanding that all is Brahman, is \n&gt; like a person climb=\r\ning the mountain and watching the top from time to \n&gt; time to correct one&#39;s=\r\n course. He will eventually reach the pinnacle. \n&gt; Karma and gyaana need to=\r\n go hand in hand and are definitely not \n&gt; opposites or alternatives. \n&gt; \n&gt;=\r\n &gt; is free from all the faults of samsaraf samsara, one does not find any \n=\r\n&gt; &gt; benefit out \n&gt; &gt; of actions which he has done or which he has to do. \n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; Actions with attachment (i.e. actions with agyaana) can be criticized \n=\r\n&gt; and dismissed. But detached actions (i.e. actions with gyaana) should be =\r\n\n&gt; encouraged. \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; This equating of liberation =\r\nand spiritual progress with akarma \n&gt; (inaction), instead of detached actio=\r\nn (nishkaama karma), is what led to \n&gt; the temporary downfall of Sanatana D=\r\nharma in the world. This is \n&gt; pseudo-Vedanta and not the real deal. \n&gt; \n&gt; =\r\nAs long as you self-identify with a body, desires arise from time to \n&gt; tim=\r\ne. The purer your conditioning is, the more dharmik those desires \n&gt; will b=\r\ne. Perform the best action within your capability to fulfil those \n&gt; desire=\r\ns. Once action is done, surrender it to the Lord and do not think \n&gt; about =\r\nit anymore. Whatever result comes, take it as God&#39;s will and do \n&gt; not regr=\r\net or rejoice. No pride and no shame. As you do this more and \n&gt; more, your=\r\n conditioning will drop more and more and your consciousness \n&gt; will become=\r\n purer and purer. Your conscience will speak louder and \n&gt; louder and your =\r\nsense of dharma will be refined. Your desires will \n&gt; become more and more =\r\ndharmik. You will transition from fulfilling dharma \n&gt; towards individual s=\r\nelf to fulfilling dharma towards universal self. \n&gt; Eventually, you will re=\r\nach a stage where you perform actions with no \n&gt; identification. Then actio=\r\nn become non-action. \n&gt; \n&gt; Vishnu, Shiva, rishis etc also do not engage in =\r\ninaction. Instead, they \n&gt; engage in detached action for maintaining and su=\r\npporting the Cosmic \n&gt; Order, as determined by the Supreme Cosmic Being and=\r\n His Shakti (his \n&gt; Kinetic aspect). \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; One =\r\nacts only when there is desire. A desireless man, whose desires \n&gt; &gt; have b=\r\neen \n&gt; &gt; fulfilled, who has risen above desires, whose desire is the atman,=\r\n has \n&gt; &gt; no \n&gt; &gt; necessity to act. \n&gt; \n&gt; First of all, everybody whose sel=\r\nf-identification with a body remains \n&gt; atleast to a small extent IS perfor=\r\nming actions continually. At the bare \n&gt; minimum, one performs actions like=\r\n breathing, eating, drinking water, \n&gt; urinating and defecating, which affe=\r\nct the lives of millions of \n&gt; micro-organisms. \n&gt; \n&gt; Second, one &quot;whose de=\r\nsire is the atman&quot; still needs to perform actions \n&gt; to fulfil that desire =\r\nand be established in atman always. Running away \n&gt; from actions and samsar=\r\na will not free one from samsara. \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Sannyas=\r\na is absolutely necessary whether it be vividisha-sannyasa or \n&gt; &gt; vidvat-s=\r\nannyasa. \n&gt; &gt; Without perfect renunciation it is impossible to pursue the p=\r\nath of \n&gt; &gt; Brahmavidya. ... \n&gt; &gt; it is foolish to cite instances of Janaka=\r\n and others who did not take \n&gt; &gt; sannyasa but \n&gt; &gt; possessed Brahmajnana. =\r\nSuch instances are quoted by householders who \n&gt; &gt; are unwilling \n&gt; &gt; to le=\r\nave their attachments, for there is no reason why they should \n&gt; &gt; stick to=\r\n \n&gt; &gt; household life after attaining knowledge. For knowledge by its very \n=\r\n&gt; &gt; nature is \n&gt; &gt; against all senses of worldly duty and activity. \n&gt; \n&gt; Y=\r\nes, many people who quote such examples may indeed be unwilling to \n&gt; leave=\r\n their attachments and take sannyasa. However, it is not correct to \n&gt; thin=\r\nk that external sannyasa is a must for Self-knowledge. In fact, \n&gt; Vasishth=\r\na gave so many criteria and paths towards Self-knowledge in \n&gt; &quot;Yoga Vaasis=\r\nhtham&quot;, but did not say that you have take sannyasa. \n&gt; \n&gt; In fact, there i=\r\ns an interesting story given by Vasishtha in that \n&gt; Vedanta epic. See the =\r\nstory of Chudala and Sikhidhwaja. King Sikhidhwaja \n&gt; leaves his wife and k=\r\ningdom, becomes an ascetic, lives in a small hut in \n&gt; a forest for a few d=\r\necades and spends all his time in meditation. Wife \n&gt; Chudala rules kingdom=\r\n on behalf of her husband and becomes \n&gt; Self-realized. She later helps her=\r\n husband in realization! So much for \n&gt; sannyasa being &quot;absolutely necessar=\r\ny&quot; for Brahmavidya! \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; The sannyasin can fin=\r\nd adequate leisure and freedom from the \n&gt; &gt; distractions of life. \n&gt; &gt; Ren=\r\nunciation is desirable even to those who have not attained jnana. \n&gt; &gt; Only=\r\n the \n&gt; &gt; sannyasin can devote the whole time for meditation. Householders =\r\n\n&gt; &gt; cannot give \n&gt; &gt; themselves up completely for meditation. \n&gt; \n&gt; :-) If=\r\n one can find some focus despire the distractions, one progresses \n&gt; faster=\r\n. If one has no jnana and mind tends to get distracted, then \n&gt; sannyasa ma=\r\ny not help that much. Merely having more free time will not \n&gt; allow one to=\r\n focus on god. One will get all kinds of thoughts when \n&gt; meditating. \n&gt; \n&gt;=\r\n For example, we see sannyasins getting caught engaging in sexual \n&gt; scanda=\r\nls and political scandals now-a-days. We see sannyasins fighting \n&gt; among t=\r\nhemselves cheaply, to become the heads of their mathas \n&gt; (monasteries). We=\r\n see sannyasins trying to raise their profile among \n&gt; devotees and politic=\r\nians or to get better TRPs on TV. We see sannyasins \n&gt; running after siddhi=\r\ns and talking about siddhis like a child may talk \n&gt; about chocolates. We s=\r\nee sannyasins trying to raise a lot of money for \n&gt; their mathas and resort=\r\ning to cheap gimmicks for it. When people not \n&gt; ready for sannyasa and hav=\r\ning dense conditioning take up sannyasa to \n&gt; have more &quot;leisure&quot; or escape=\r\n from &quot;the distractions of life&quot;, this is \n&gt; what happens! \n&gt; \n&gt; Remain in =\r\nthe material world and do sadhana. Develop detachment from \n&gt; body and indi=\r\nvidual needs, compassion to others, dispassion and \n&gt; detachment in actions=\r\n, surrender to the Lord and the ability to engage \n&gt; in powerful actions wh=\r\nile being absolutely prepared for any end result. \n&gt; As you make progress, =\r\nperhaps oneday you will be ready for sannyasa and \n&gt; it will just happen. O=\r\nr perhaps you will become realized even without \n&gt; sannyasa. In either case=\r\n, the end goal is internal detachment and \n&gt; self-realization and not exter=\r\nnal renunciation. \n&gt; \n&gt; Anybody who tells you that a *specific* external ac=\r\ntion or object is a \n&gt; *must* for internal purification and liberation is o=\r\nver-selling it. \n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        * \n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Without abandonment of th=\r\ne concerns of worldly life, knowledge cannot \n&gt; &gt; be pursued \n&gt; &gt; with unab=\r\nated vigor and devotion. It does not mean that the sannyasin \n&gt; &gt; undervalu=\r\nes \n&gt; &gt; human society and discards all men without helping them at all. As =\r\nthe \n&gt; &gt; life of a \n&gt; &gt; sannyasin is meant only to reach the highest Realit=\r\ny, and as he has \n&gt; &gt; already passed \n&gt; &gt; through the lower stages of spiri=\r\ntual evolution, he may appear to be \n&gt; &gt; not working \n&gt; &gt; for the rest of h=\r\numanity at large; but it is to be borne in mind that \n&gt; &gt; he exercises \n&gt; &gt;=\r\n a silent and unnoticed but powerful influence for the good of the \n&gt; &gt; pub=\r\nlic. That \n&gt; &gt; itself is the service he is rendering to the society and tha=\r\nt is the \n&gt; &gt; highest and \n&gt; &gt; the most beneficent service that one could e=\r\nver do to man. One who is \n&gt; &gt; intent upon \n&gt; &gt; realizing the peace, the bl=\r\niss, the One Without a Second=C3=83=C2=A2=C3=A2=C2=AC&quot;Shantam, \n&gt; &gt; Shivam,=\r\n \n&gt; &gt; Advaitam=C3=83=C2=A2=C3=A2=C2=AC&quot;is the most powerful and the useful =\r\nfriend of the world! \n&gt; \n&gt; Correct. But, not every sannyasin may have enoug=\r\nh &quot;spiritual evolution&quot; \n&gt; to exert such &quot;powerful influence for the good o=\r\nf the public&quot;. The \n&gt; question here is not whether one has renounced X, Y, =\r\nZ external things \n&gt; or not. The question is whether one has renounced ego,=\r\n doership of one&#39;s \n&gt; actions and surrendered to the Supreme Cosmic Being c=\r\nompletely or not. \n&gt; One who has, whoever he is and wherever he is, has a h=\r\nighly purified \n&gt; consciousness and exerts a powerful subtle influence on t=\r\nhe world. \n&gt; \n&gt; Best regards, \n&gt; Narasimha \n&gt; -----------------------------=\r\n----------------------------- \n&gt;    Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Les=\r\nsons, Jyotish Writings, \n&gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam =\r\nand Pitri Tarpana: \n&gt